    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You get a sense of the best way to interact with the target to encourage positive regard toward you. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Charisma checks, Charismabased skill checks, and Sense Motive checks you attempt when interacting with the target. In addition, when you fail a Charisma check or Charisma-based skill check when interacting with the target, you can reroll the check as a reaction. However, if you attempt the reroll, the target receives a new saving throw against the spell. Taking hostile action against the target automatically ends the spell.&nbsp;</span></p>",
